qas.question: Which Russian rocket carries passengers to and from the International Space Station?

context: The Russian <a0_0>R-7 rocket<a0_0/> family, which launched the first Sputnik at the beginning of the space race, is still in use today. It services the International Space Station (ISS) as the launcher for both the Soyuz and Progress spacecraft. It also ferries both Russian and American crews to and from the station.
